  "issue_title": "MCP config validator extracts the wrong package name for `npm exec`/`npm x` with a `--` separator (and falsely errors on `npx -- <pkg>`)",
  "issue_body": "**Labels:** bug, mcp\n**Component:** `apps/web` \u2014 MCP config validator\n**Affected file:** `apps/web/src/lib/mcp-config-validator.ts` (`packageFromRunner` lines 246\u2013278; `packageFromNpxArgs` lines 238\u2013244; consumed at lines 372 and 425)\n\n## Summary\n\n`packageFromRunner` extracts the runnable package name from an MCP server's `command` + `args`. Its per\u2011runner handling of the `--` separator is **inconsistent**, and the `npm` branch is **backwards**:\n\n- **npx** (`packageFromNpxArgs`, line 240) keeps the tokens **before** `--`: `args.slice(0, stopAt)` \u2014 so `npx <pkg> -- <args>` \u2192 `<pkg>`. Correct.\n- **npm** (line 264) keeps the tokens **after** `--`: `scopedArgs.slice(separatorIndex + 1)` \u2014 so `npm exec <pkg> -- <args>` drops the package and returns the *package's* arguments, which are then filtered out as flags \u2192 **`\"\"`**.\n- **pnpm / yarn** (line 256) take the first non\u2011flag token and never special\u2011case `--`. Because `--` starts with `-`, it is filtered out automatically, so this branch is actually **correct for both `<pkg> -- <args>` and `-- <pkg>`**.\n\nIn `npm exec`/`npm x`, the package name is the first non\u2011flag operand; everything after `--` are arguments forwarded **to** the package. Slicing *after* `--` therefore discards the package.\n\n## Reproduced\n\n```\npackageFromRunner(\"npm\", [\"exec\", \"my-package\", \"--\", \"--verbose\"])  -> \"\"           (expected \"my-package\")\npackageFromRunner(\"npm\", [\"x\", \"@scope/pkg\", \"--\", \"-y\"])            -> \"\"           (expected \"@scope/pkg\")\npackageFromRunner(\"npm\", [\"exec\", \"my-package\"])                     -> \"my-package\" (ok)\npackageFromRunner(\"npx\", [\"my-package\", \"--\", \"--verbose\"])          -> \"my-package\" (ok \u2014 npm should match this)\n```\n\nSecondary defect from the same root cause \u2014 `packageFromNpxArgs` slices *before* `--`, so the `npx -- <pkg>` form yields `\"\"`:\n\n```\npackageFromRunner(\"npx\", [\"--\", \"my-package\"])                       -> \"\"\n```\n\nand that empty result then trips a **false error** at lines 373\u2013378:\n\n```ts\nif ([\"npx\", \"uvx\", \"bunx\"].includes(command.toLowerCase()) && !packageName) {\n  errors.push(`${command} server is missing a package name in args.`);\n}\n```\n\nso a valid `npx -- my-package` MCP server is reported as \u201cmissing a package name\u201d.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nThe extracted package is the first **operand** (first non\u2011flag token) of the runner invocation, regardless of where `--` sits:\n\n| Input | Expected |\n|-------|----------|\n| `npm exec my-package -- --verbose` | `my-package` |\n| `npm x @scope/pkg -- -y` | `@scope/pkg` |\n| `npm exec -- my-package` | `my-package` |\n| `npx my-package -- --flag` | `my-package` |\n| `npx -- my-package` | `my-package` |\n\n## Impact\n\n`packageFromRunner` feeds:\n- the validation result's `packageName` field (line 425), surfaced to the user and used downstream to identify/display the server's package; and\n- the \u201cmissing a package name\u201d error gate (lines 372\u2013378).\n\nSo a common, valid `npm exec <pkg> -- <args>` MCP server config is reported with a **blank package name**, and a valid `npx -- <pkg>` config is **rejected with a spurious error**. Both are reachable from ordinary user\u2011pasted configs.\n\n## Root cause\n\nThe `--` separator is treated as a *boundary to slice around* (before it for npx, after it for npm) instead of as a non\u2011operand token. The package is simply the first operand; `--` is never the package. The pnpm/yarn branch already encodes this correctly (filter flags, take the first remaining token), because `--` is filtered as a flag.\n\n## Proposed fix\n\nUnify all subcommand runners on the operand\u2011first rule the pnpm/yarn branch already uses \u2014 the first token that is neither a flag nor the `--` separator \u2014 so the package is found whether it sits before or after `--`:\n\n```ts\n// First package operand of a runner's args: the first token that is neither a\n// flag nor the `--` separator. Works whether the package precedes the separator\n// (`<runner> pkg -- args`) or follows it (`<runner> -- pkg`).\nfunction firstPackageOperand(args: string[]) {\n  return args.find((arg) => arg && arg !== \"--\" && !arg.startsWith(\"-\")) || \"\";\n}\n\nfunction packageFromRunner(command: string, args: string[]) {\n  const lower = command.toLowerCase();\n  if (lower.endsWith(\"npx\") || lower === \"npx\") return firstPackageOperand(args);\n  if ([\"uvx\", \"bunx\"].includes(lower)) return firstPackageOperand(args);\n  if (lower === \"pnpm\" || lower === \"yarn\") {\n    const dlxIndex = args.findIndex((arg) => arg === \"dlx\");\n    return firstPackageOperand(dlxIndex >= 0 ? args.slice(dlxIndex + 1) : args);\n  }\n  if (lower === \"npm\") {\n    const runnerIndex = args.findIndex((arg) => [\"exec\", \"x\"].includes(arg));\n    return firstPackageOperand(\n      runnerIndex >= 0 ? args.slice(runnerIndex + 1) : args,\n    );\n  }\n  if (lower === \"docker\") {\n    const runIndex = args.findIndex((arg) => arg === \"run\");\n    return runIndex >= 0 ? firstPackageOperand(args.slice(runIndex + 1)) : \"\";\n  }\n  return \"\";\n}\n```\n\nThis removes the divergent before/after\u2011`--` slicing, makes every runner consistent, and fixes both the `npm exec <pkg> -- <args>` blank\u2011package case and the `npx -- <pkg>` false error. (`packageFromNpxArgs` can be inlined/removed.)\n\n## Acceptance criteria / test plan\n\n`tests/mcp-config-validator.test.ts` covers only the `dlx` form (line 308) and has no `npm exec`/`--`/`-- <pkg>` cases \u2014 the bug is unpinned. Add:\n\n- [ ] `command: \"npm\", args: [\"exec\", \"my-package\", \"--\", \"--verbose\"]` \u2192 `packageName === \"my-package\"`.\n- [ ] `command: \"npm\", args: [\"x\", \"@scope/pkg\", \"--\", \"-y\"]` \u2192 `\"@scope/pkg\"`.\n- [ ] `command: \"npm\", args: [\"exec\", \"--\", \"my-package\"]` \u2192 `\"my-package\"`.\n- [ ] `command: \"npx\", args: [\"--\", \"my-package\"]` \u2192 `\"my-package\"` and **no** \u201cmissing a package name\u201d error.\n- [ ] Existing cases stay green: `npx my-package -- --flag` \u2192 `\"my-package\"`; `pnpm`/`yarn` `dlx @example/mcp-server` \u2192 `\"@example/mcp-server\"`.\n\n## Notes for reviewers\n\n- Verified against `main`: `packageFromRunner(\"npm\", [\"exec\",\"my-package\",\"--\",\"--verbose\"])` returns `\"\"`; the npx path returns `\"my-package\"` for the same shape, confirming the inconsistency.\n- Searched open/closed issues and PRs on `JSONbored/awesome-claude` \u2014 no existing report of the `--` extraction bug. Related but distinct: #1076/#1080 (warn on *unpinned* package runners) and #855 (localhost handling). Distinct from previously filed issues (atob, notifications truncate, seo k\u2011suffix, keyword normalization, command\u2011safety pipe\u2011to\u2011shell #1785).\n",
